values = [

    {"value": "10 days", "question": "Is the time less than a week?"},
    {"value": "daily", "question": "Is the time less than a week?"},
    {"value": "2 hours", "question": "Is the time less than a week?"},

    {"value": "Lakers", "question": "Basketball team?"},
    {"value": "Nuggets", "question": "Basketball team?"},
    {"value": "Dodgers", "question": "Basketball team?"},
    {"value": "Mets", "question": "Basketball team?"},

    {"value": "DeAndre' Bembry", "question": "Return the nationality of the player."},
    {"value": "Denzel Valentine", "question": "Return the nationality of the player."},
    {"value": "Deyonta Davis", "question": "Return the nationality of the player."},
    {"value": "Domantas Sabonis", "question": "Return the nationality of the player."},
    {"value": "E'Twaun Moore", "question": "Return the nationality of the player."},
]

# Define a function to answer each question
def answer_question(value):
    if value["question"] == "Total penalty count?":
        # Split the value by spaces and get the last part
        penalty_count = value["value"].split(" ")[-1]
        # Remove the parentheses and convert to int
        return str(int(penalty_count.replace("(", "").replace(")", "")))
    elif value["question"] == "Is the time less than a week?":
        # Convert the value to days
        time_in_days = 0
        if "days" in value["value"]:
            time_in_days = int(value["value"].replace(" days", ""))
        elif "hours" in value["value"]:
            time_in_days = int(value["value"].replace(" hours", "")) / 24
        # Check if the time is less than a week
        return str(time_in_days < 7)
    elif value["question"] == "Basketball team?":
        # Check if the value is a basketball team
        basketball_teams = ["Lakers", "Nuggets"]
        return str(value["value"] in basketball_teams)
    elif value["question"] == "Return the nationality of the player.":
        # Get the nationality from the player's name
        nationality = value["value"].split("'")[0]
        return nationality

# Answer each question and print the results
for value in values:
    print(answer_question(value), end="
